Miss <b>Madge Raymond Lesher</b>, a daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Raymond Lesher of Park Avenue, New York City, was introduced to society in 1915.  A member of the Junior League, she was active in war relief work.  She married Lieutenant Charles Singleton Bartow, Jr., U.S.N., also of New York City, on October 16, 1920. Mr. Bartow was a 1916 graduate of Columbia University. 
